@page "/documentation/port-scanner"

<PageTitle>Port Scanner Docs - XNet›</PageTitle>


<main class="container-apple main-page">
    <div class="doc-wrapper">
        <DocSidebar />
        
        <div class="doc-main-content animate-fade">
            <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-4">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/documentation" class="link-blue" style="font-size: 14px;">Documentation</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active text-muted" style="font-size: 14px;" aria-current="page">Port Scanner</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>

            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-white mb-4">Port Scanner</h1>
            <p class="hero-description mb-5">Identify active services and audit device security with rapid sequencing.</p>

            <!-- Visual Preview -->
            <div class="glass-card overflow-hidden mb-5">
                <img src="assets/screenshots/port.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Port Scanner Interface" />
            </div>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">Service Auditing</h2>
                <p class="text-sf-secondary">The Port Scanner allows for targeted auditing of specific IP addresses. By checking common (or custom) TCP/UDP ports, you can quickly determine which services are exposed to the network.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">Port Range Rules</h2>
                <p class="text-sf-secondary mb-3">Define the scope of your audit using flexible port selection logic:</p>
                <div class="bg-dark p-3 rounded mb-4" style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3) !important;">
                    <ul class="text-sf-secondary list-unstyled m-0" style="font-family: 'SF Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px;">
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-primary">80, 443, 8080</span> — <span class="text-muted">Comma-separated list (Targeted)</span></li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><span class="text-primary">1-1024</span> — <span class="text-muted">Range Notation (Well-known ports)</span></li>
                        <li><span class="text-primary">22</span> — <span class="text-muted">Single service check</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">Security Focus</h2>
                <ul class="text-sf-secondary">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Custom Ranges</strong>: Scan specific ports or entire blocks (1-65535).</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Service ID</strong>: Logic that helps identify standard services like HTTP, SSH, Telnet, and SNMP.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Timeout Logic</strong>: Precision timeout handling to prevent skewed results during high-latency scans.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>
